race.comment: LADY BOSS (6) comes across from NSW after beginning her career with Ciaron Maher. She's trialled impressively since arriving in WA and Pike hops in the saddle for her WA debut. Maps beautifully and can make an impression first up. HEDAWOOD (11) jumped favourite last start in a similar race last time out and flew home to be 2L off the winner. He's likely to get back from the draw, but he's building nicely and can storm over the top. RECONNAISSANCE (13) bolted in over this trip at Bunbury on Cup Day to shed the maiden tag, winning by 2.5L. Makes the jump in grade today, but he maps well and looks open to plenty of improvement now. Can build on his first-up performance. DUBAI'S DAUGHTER (12) led and won a CL3 here on Cup Day and can be prominent in the run once again. Can give them something to chase. TYCOON HARRY (2) just missed in a much stronger race first-up and can be in the finish second-up.
